column1: Fast & Free Full Length Tight Nulux 28"
column6: I've never been one to wear pants/tights/capris (as I'm a speed shorts fan) but due to some really cold weather, my legs needed covering. I bought these because of the color (dark sport red) and the first time I wore them absolutely fell in love with them. You truly feel like you are wearing nothing and the tights DO NOT get in your way - free movement for sure! I've since purchased about six more of the Fast & Free and haven't worn shorts since. Thrilled to have found these as I LOVE them!

column1: Fast & Free Full Length Tight Nulux 28"
column6:
I love these leggings. I received them as a birthday gift. I normally wear a size 6-8, so when I received a size 6 as a gift - the tighter fit was perfect. I did not experience negative stretching issues listed by other reviewers. The side pockets are amazingly convenient. I wear these leggings for long-distance running. They are so light that it feels like you're running naked - in the best way. I ran my first SeaWheeze Half Marathon in these puppies last September and they were great.
*However, after a year of consistent wear (and despite washing them religiously as directed), they are now pilling at the inner seams and the stitching is coming undone in the inner thigh area. I now check the stitching in the inner thigh area every time that I put these on because I feel like its a matter of days before a hole comes to fruition. This is very sad because I am used to lululemon clothing lasting many years. So, for the high price that these leggings fetched (from my gift-givers), it feels disappointing that they will need to be replaced very soon. Although I love these leggings, I feel the love slowly drifting out of reach. Due to the disappointing life span, I will be considering other lululemon leggings to replace these ones.

I decided to order another size 6 but in a different line and it’s the same problem. They won’t stay up! My daughter got a size 4 as a gift and I borrowed those for a Crossfit workout and they didn’t budge, didn’t have to pull them up once. Now I have three

column5: Great tights, but Dark Sport Red is... not!
column6:
I love the Fast and Free's! The nulux is a really stretchy fabric, and the high rise on these babies are just that - so high. They stay up relatively well through burpees and any Crossfit workouts I've put them through. I've also worn them for a 10k, and they stayed up with my phone in the side pocket. I suggest a smaller size when purchasing.
BUT! When I saw these go on sale, I bought my usual size and waited patiently for them to arrive at my door. But my dark sport red is not red - it is definitely a burnt orange. They DO NOT look like the colour on the site. And they're a final sale... *sigh*.
I've been swearing by Lulu everything lately - hope you guys find a better way to communicate your product online.

column6: I was so excited to find these leggings!I have a been a huge Lululemon fan for a couple years now and when a friend of mine wore some leggings to our gym by a competitor - I fell in love with her side pockets. I thought "That would be so convenient for my cell phone & stopwatch while I'm training clients!" Being the dedicated Lulu-fan that I am, I was ECSTATIC to find some made my Lululemon. I ordered my normal size and while the material & stitching, I feel, was wonderful; it only took 2 days of wear to change my opinion. While they fit my waist perfectly, they feel "larger" in the hip and thigh area and I am forced to constantly pull them up--regardless of whether or not I have belongings in the pockets. I wonder If I should have gone to a smaller size or if that would create the opposite of my current conundrum. Super sad about this situation as I probably will get little to no further wear from them - I wanted so bad to love these!

column1: Fast & Free Full Length Tight Nulux 28"
column6: I loved how it fits and the cut that compliments my body. The fabric is super soft, light and stretchy. But being that stretchy makes the pattern stretch out and show a bit whitish where you have curves, and when u bend (squat), but its definitely not see-through. The pocket also stretches a lot and pulls the fabric when the phone is placed there (would have noticed it in the photos if I paid enough attention before purchasing. Look at the images with a phone in the model's pocket). Also the pockets are too deep that my phone slides to almost near my knee. I think in general its good to pay attention to what it was made for: "Running". But I tried it in the gym during my strength training and It does stay in place well, and passed the test. I also find myself sweat more in these pants comparing to full-on luxtreme as the fabric feels warmer to me. It also feels longer comparing to the other lulu 7/8 leggings I have. Putting aside the fact that they went on 50% sale right after I got them, I find them pricy for what they are, comparing to my other leggings.

column1: Fast & Free Full Length Tight Nulux 28"
column6: I received this gift from a friend who already had a few pairs and LOVED the way it fits. Never had a lulu product before until this year, but like previous reviews it seems to be a problem with the seams near the crotch/back side coming undone? Treated this pair like gold, but sad to see after less than a year of casually wearing it and wearing during work outs, the side seams started to fray and there was pilling around the sides... and now a hole at the crotch from the seams.. Other than those problems and the price those are the only things holding me back from buying another pair of these. They are a great fit, flattering and didn't slide down from me at all. Everywhere I went I got compliments on my leggings.

column1: Fast & Free Full Length Tight Nulux 28"
column5: Awesome pants - here are suggestions on colors
column6:
Dear lululemon,
Thank you for creating my permanent addiction to the fast and free tights. I have half of my running leggings drawer deducted just to the fast and free tights because they feel like second skin, very soft, have tons of pockets and flatter the legs. They are perfect for any high intensity exercises especially running.
Personal thank you for releasing a longer version in 28, I finally have pairs that go all the way to my socks and there is just a small slit of skin that I see depending on how high are my socks (I am 5’7). Now, of course, naturally, I have to rebuy all my favorite colors in this long version. I have already stocked up on black, nocturnal teal and green camo. Dark sport red is no go for me personally because it is an orangy brick color and I do not like orange; if you have sold a dark red, not dark sport red, I would probably would get it. Surprisingly, my favorite pair is now the green camo even though I am not a green camo person per se. It is so beautiful that I reach for them first.
Please, release more colors in this 28 length. Just some ideas for you: true navy, midnight navy, titanium or some other beautiful dark grey (please-please), melantine (?), black/grey camo preferably sequia camo but I will take savana camo too (please-please!), dark olive, pacific teal, black cherry, phantom, some dusty pink color such as quicksand, dark red, ... should I continue or you have gotten a hint, wink-wink?

column1: Fast & Free Full Length Tight Nulux 28"
column6: This is my first lululemon purchase and I am thoroughly impressed. Take it with a grain of salt however, because I have no other LLL leggings to compare them to that speaks for quality comparisons. My favorites for the last few years have been the Knockout tights from Victoria's Secret, but I think I may even like these better. Which I better, for double the price lol. The material is not cotton at all, so they're not a direct comparison to that pant. I am 6'0" with a curvy build and these fit me perfectly. They are high rise with some length to spare at the bottom, so if you're shorter than me, you may have to get them hemmed. I'd say they provide more than light coverage because I feel held in quite well without feeling stuffed. They are 100% squat proof as well; I can't see anything when I bend over, even with direct light. They feel so comfortable and soft on my legs. They do make a swishing sound if your legs rub together, but it doesn't bother me at all. I'd buy these again for sure, even if I never try another type from lulu.

column6:
I bought two pair of these in black and purple in May. They stretched out and the front seam in the front frayed within four months of wear. Very disappointing.
Love the design and all of the great areas to store your phone, key, credit card etc. Price was high, but I thought it was worth it because of the great style and comfort. Love the white dots on the leg. I sized down as advised by sales clerk and washed according to directions she gave. They looked and felt great, unfortunately, they did not stand up to the test of time. They stretched out and the front seam looked llike the tread just came apart. I'm sorry to say this purchase was a huge disappointment.

column1: Fast & Free Full Length Tight Nulux 28"
column5: had to pull my underwear up constantly with these
column6: I really wanted to love these pants, and based on the good reviews I may have just gotten unlucky with my purchase - except it wasn't just on one occasion. I've never had this happen in the 10 years I've been buying lululemon. Lulu is nearly my entire wardrobe. My destination was 8 blocks away, and a few blocks in I found my underwear needed constant pulling up - like falling down! I walk a lot in San Francisco and I was pretty horrified the rest of the evening constantly checking myself. What was happening should be impossible with these pants. I bought my usual size 4. Clearly the compression on these don't work, and I could feel it loose all around in that hug-but-not-quite-hugging kind of way. I started off with black, loved them, and purchase a second pair immediately in purple. Now both are doing the same thing. At $128 a pop (more expensive than usual pair of bottoms), this is unacceptable. I have never complained before, just lived with defects on this item and then that one, but more and more items I've been buying recently are having issues and I'm finally speaking out. ahhh!!! {{frustrated lulu-lover}}

column6: Love Fast n Free tights they are my favorite of all time! I will say I went with my normal size and they were a little snug, not enough to size differently though! column1: Fast & Free Full Length Tight Nulux 28"
column6: I have five pairs of the fast and free 25" tight - I'm obsessed with them. I have to agree with other reviewers that these run much smaller than the crop and 25". My normal size is a 2 but now I'm pregnant so I've been wearing 4s (5'4" 120lbs pre-preg). Since the size 4 was sold out I bought the 2 assuming I can wear them post pregnancy. The good news is that even though they're probably a size too small on me, the stretched out pattern doesn't look weird or stop them from being squat proof. I really hope they restock the sold out sizes because I absolutely love the camo. I would love the red and black camo that guys stuff comes in!

column1: Fast & Free Full Length Tight Nulux 28"
column5: Very long, but ohhhhh so CAMO!
column6: First of all, I LOVE camo! I have the inspire crops in the green and blue camo that were released several years ago. I have worn them to death! I also want to say I LOVE the Fast & Free II crops and own 10 pairs. They are the perfect fit and length for me (120, 42-27-36, 5'8) in a size 6. I have tried the Fast & Free II 25" tight and now this 28" pant. Ironically, the tights and pants are too long. The pants have about 2" of extra length which is odd since they are listed as 28". I have a 30" inseam and I am a tall person. I will be keeping them since I love the print even though they are scrunched up at the ankles. I would have them hemmed shorter, but like the 25" tights I already own, I can tell the diameter around the ankle is too wide. In addition to the length, they do fit a bit differently than the crop or tight (on my body type, tall, lean, runner). I have tried to size down to a 4, but they are so tight I can barely get them on. I like my pants snug, but not squeezing me all day long (I wear them all day for my job). They are tighter around the waist and they do seem to ride up a little in the crotch. I haven't had this issue with the crops. Again, this is not enough for me to send them back. I am just picky after owning enough pairs of LLL crops, tights and pants to rival the GDP of a small country.
